holar-activism to be complex, diverse, and multi-faceted, and paying particular attention to how scholar-activists grapple with their own complicities in the harms perpetrated and perpetuated by Higher Education institutions, this book is a call to arms for academics who are, or want to be, committed to social justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnti-racism. 0aMinorities in higher educationzGreat Britain. 0aMinority activistszGreat Britain. 0aRacism in higher educationzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Race & Ethnic Relations.2bisacsh  aUK Higher Education.  aanti-racism.  ahigher education.  aneoliberalism.  aracial justice.  ascholar-activism.  asocial justice.  auniversities.1 aConnelly, Laura, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aConnelly, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoseph-Salisbury, Remi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198840uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615797340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526157973423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526157973/original  a978-3-11-128198-8  Manchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packageb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles